        {
            "id": "78961d0dc6c94d09b7eb9",
            "questionText": "A construction crane is designed to lift heavy loads while maintaining rotational equilibrium. The crane pivots at a point where a steel beam with a weight of $!$150 \\mathrm{ kN}$!$ is located $!$20 \\mathrm{ m}$!$ from the pivot. To counteract this load, a counterweight is placed on the opposite side of the pivot at a horizontal distance of $!$8 \\mathrm{ m}$!$. Calculate the mass (in kg) of the required counterweight, assuming an acceleration due to gravity of $!$9.81 \\mathrm{ m/s^2}$!$.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "3880ad49078648139d935",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying the fundamental principle used for rotational equilibrium. Which of the following formulas represents the principle where the sum of the moments around a pivot is zero?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "b740ddfa-3ad8-4e38-b850-124c5bb429fe",
                        "259589dd-4c8e-4938-9dde-4a0c9930e92e"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\text{Moment} = \\text{Force} \\times \\text{Distance}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$F = ma$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\text{Weight} = \\text{mass} \\times \\text{gravity}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "4288f472e26045529fba3",
                    "stepText": "Next, calculate the moment produced by the steel beam. Convert the beam\u2019s weight from kilonewtons to newtons and multiply it by its distance from the pivot. What is the moment (in $!$Nm$!$) created by the beam?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "3000000"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "Nm",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "c021eadd-5a2d-4fa7-bd9a-8c7c7cfb939c"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "255d29b6e91d43769364b",
                    "stepText": "Now, consider the counterweight side. The counterweight produces a moment given by its weight ($!$mg$!$) times its distance from the pivot. Which of the following formulas correctly represents the moment due to the counterweight?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "c021eadd-5a2d-4fa7-bd9a-8c7c7cfb939c"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$m \\times g \\times d$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$m \\times \\frac{g}{d}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\frac{m}{g \\times d}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
